A healthy 3-node RabbitMQ cluster is running in the karma-rabbitmq-security-upgrade-v2-01-ca2a415e-cluster-a
namespace on RabbitMQ 3.12.

Upgrade the cluster to RabbitMQ version 3.12 using only
native Kubernetes resources (StatefulSet, Service, PVC, Secret, ConfigMap,
etc). Do not use any CRD, Operator, or third-party controller.

Requirements:
- Preserve existing queue data.
- Keep the cluster healthy with 3 nodes.

Goal:
- All nodes run RabbitMQ version 3.12 (or a patch release
  within that version family).
- /app vhost and app-queue still exist with messages.
- Cluster remains healthy.

Cluster context:
  Namespace: karma-rabbitmq-security-upgrade-v2-01-ca2a415e-cluster-a
  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-security-upgrade-v2-01-ca2a415e-cluster-a get pods
  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-security-upgrade-v2-01-ca2a415e-cluster-a get svc
  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-security-upgrade-v2-01-ca2a415e-cluster-a get pvc
  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-security-upgrade-v2-01-ca2a415e-cluster-a logs <pod>---
